<HEADLINE>
FT  02 OCT 93 / Finance and the Family: Dollar waxes against D-Mark - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE US dollar strengthened against the D-Mark this week, after being lifted
by positive US economic data on Thursday, but it fell back a little on
Friday after further statistics which were not as good as expected. Worries
over the political situation in Moscow had depressed the D-Mark, although in
the middle of the week economic concerns took over.
