<HEADLINE>
FT  02 OCT 93 / Swan Hunter wins contract
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SWAN HUNTER, the Tyneside shipbuilder in receivership, has won a contract
from the Ministry of Defence for additional work on Fort George, an oil
supply ship.
The work on Fort George, which Swan Hunter handed over to the MoD in March,
is for minor adjustments. It will employ, at peak levels, 150 workers for
seven weeks.
