<HEADLINE>
FT  02 OCT 93 / Sellafield gas power plant
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
HYDRO-ELECTRIC, the Scottish power utility, and British Nuclear Fuels, the
state-owned nuclear services company, are to build a small gas-fired power
station at BNF's site at Sellafield, Cumbria.
The 157MW combined heat and power plant is expected to become fully
operational next year.
The plant will be run by a jointly owned company, Fellside Heat and Power,
using gas supplied by British Gas. It will supply steam and heat to
Sellafield and about 100MW of electricity to Hydro-Electric.
