<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / London Stock Exchange: Forte down on figures
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and SAQIB QURESHI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
INTERIM results from Forte prompted a series of broker downgrades and sent
the stock tumbling 10 to 227p in reasonable turnover of 5.1m. Leisure
analysts said they believed the shares to be in for a fairly dull time for
the next few months as the hotel group revealed its recovery was proving
much slower than had been expected.
The shares have run up in recent months as the leisure sector's chief
recovery play, but talk of a slower revival saw some brokers yesterday
change their recommendations from 'buy' to 'hold'.
Profits came in at the low end of expectations and, together with Forte's
cautious outlook, led brokers' forecasts down by some 15 per cent to around
Pounds 90m. At this level the dividend would be uncovered, prompting further
speculation that the group will at some stage launch a long-rumoured rights
issue.
