<TEXT>
RHONE-POULENC, the French chemicals group, is negotiating an increase in its
stake in Institut Merieux, a producer of human and animal vaccines, writes
John Ridding.
Shares in Institut Merieux have been suspended pending a further
announcement on the planned deal.
Rhone Poulenc currently holds 51 per cent of the shares with the Merieux
family holding 16 per cent, the Dassault family holding 14 per cent, and the
balance being controlled by the public and the Pasteur Institute.
Chemicals industry analysts said that Rhone-Poulenc wants to increase its
holding in Institut Merieux to integrate it more fully into its healthcare
division.
