<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / International Company News: Power Corporation loses Pounds
I103m after exceptionals
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
POWER Corporation, the Irish property group whose Trocadero Centre
development in Central London went into administrative receivership in
January, has reported a pre-tax loss of IPounds 102.8m (Pounds 98m) for the
year ending March 31st 1993, after an exceptional charge of IPounds 97m.
The charge consisted of a write-off of IPounds 54.8m on the company's
Trocadero and Island Site developments in London, and a further IPounds
42.4m of write-downs in other property values.
Excluding the charge, the loss was IPounds 4.5m compared with a profit of
IPounds 9.5m in the 1991-92 financial year. Net assets have fallen from
IPounds 223m to IPPounds 24.5m.
Mr Robin Power, chairman and chief executive, said that disposals of IPounds
14.5m have been made during the year to reduce borrowings. He said: 'As the
recession lifts so will rental incomes and property values'. The company has
98 per cent of its properties leased.
The company's portfolio of properties held for resale has increased by
IPounds 43m to IPounds 85m, primarily due to reclassification of properties
from its long-term investment portfolio. The principal asset that is up for
sale is the Ambassador Hotel in Los Angeles.
Losses per share were IPounds 88.43p, against earnings per share last year
of IPounds 9.15.
</TEXT>
