<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / UK Company News: JO Walker back in black with Pounds 0.16m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JO Walker, the timber importer, reported a return to profits in the six
months to June 30. Helped by an exceptional gain of Pounds 227,000 on the
realisation of an investment, pre-tax profits were Pounds 162,000, against
losses of Pounds 162,000.
Turnover advanced 13 per cent to Pounds 7.17m (Pounds 6.33m) for operating
profits of Pounds 15,000, compared with losses of Pounds 78,000.
Earnings per share for the six months jcame out at 20.2p (losses 19.2p).
The company said profit margins were under intense pressure resulting from
higher cost of raw materials because of sterling's devaluation.
