<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Helical Bar
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
After a significant reduction in the interest charge, Helical Bar, the
property group, reported a 75 per cent advance in pre-tax profits from
Pounds 1.27m to Pounds 2.22m for the half year to July 31.
Turnover fell from Pounds 15m to Pounds 10.9m. At the operating level
profits were down 35 per cent to Pounds 4.58m.
Over the past 18 months the group has made substantial sales, thereby
reducing borrowings, directors said. As a result gross rentals were lower at
Pounds 5.6m (Pounds 7m). Net interest payable fell by Pounds 3.93m to Pounds
2.62m.
Earnings per share worked through at 10.89p (5.01p) and the interim dividend
is raised from 2.4p to 2.5p. Directors are forecasting a 20 per cent
increase in the total.
</TEXT>
