<HEADLINE>
FT  01 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Storm
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Storm Group, the animation, licensing and merchandising company, returned to
the black with a pre-tax profit of Pounds 102,000 for the first six months
of 1993.
That compared with a deficit of Pounds 1.13m, incurred after a Pounds 1.54m
write-off in respect of film costs.
Because of the absence of any sales of completed animation productions to
the ITV network, turnover for the first half was down from Pounds 4.05m to
Pounds 1.78m. The pre-tax figure was after interest charged of Pounds 73,000
(Pounds 6,000 received).
Earnings per share were 0.14p (1.49p losses).
