FT  01 OCT 93 / UK Company News: Courtyard Leisure
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Courtyard Leisure, the wine bar and restaurant operator, reported increased
losses of Pounds 578,000 for the year to March 31, against Pounds 288,000.
The result was struck after a provision of Pounds 195,000 against the loss
on the sale of a wine bar.
Turnover was Pounds 2.22m (Pounds 1.9m). Losses per share were 5.4p (3.1p).
Mr Ali Safa, chairman, said that trading was difficult. Turnover increased
because of the acquisition of a wine bar in the City but its performance was
hit by the bombing of the nearby Baltic Exchange.
